Connect to your Amazon Linux EC2 instance using SSH.
Update the system packages:
text
sudo yum update -y

Install wget if it's not already installed:
text
sudo yum install -y wget

Download the latest version of Terraform. You can find the latest version on the official Terraform website. Here's an example using version 1.5.7 (replace with the latest version):
text
wget https://releases.hashicorp.com/terraform/1.5.7/terraform_1.5.7_linux_amd64.zip

Install unzip if it's not already installed:
text
sudo yum install -y unzip

Unzip the downloaded file:
text
unzip terraform_1.5.7_linux_amd64.zip

Move the Terraform binary to a directory in your PATH:
text
sudo mv terraform /usr/local/bin/

Verify the installation:
text
terraform version

This should display the version of Terraform you just installed.
